<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1228,1613]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1335,1360]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
The females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paramonov" authorityYear="1925" box="[503,609,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[503,526,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[542,609,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from those of other 
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1150,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1048,1150,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following combination of characters: scape and pedicel brown; flagellum orange, almost 1.8 times longer than wide and about 1.7 times longer than pedicel; frons and face with dense silvery pile; scutum with two longitudinal greyish bands of pollinosity and dense erect silvery pile; sparse pile on anterior anepisternum; legs predominantly black; mid coxa bare posteriorly; fore and mid tibiae yellowish-orange on basal half; hind tibia not broadened apically; tarsi yellowish-orange ventrally; abdomen narrow and black, abdominal tergites without lateral red or yellow maculae, tergites 2–4 with a pair of interrupted greyish pollinose fasciae. This species was collected in north and northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[304,352,1589,1612]" name="Iran" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">Iran</collectingCountry>
, close to its 
<typeStatus box="[490,538,1589,1613]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality, in 
<collectingCountry box="[670,768,1588,1613]" name="Armenia" pageId="16" pageNumber="43">Armenia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hurkmans" box="[783,968,1588,1613]" pageId="16" pageNumber="43" refString="Hurkmans, W. (1993) A monograph of Merodon (Diptera: Syrphidae). Part 1. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 136, 147 - 234." type="journal article" year="1993">Hurkmans 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
